param

Class Region

  • java.lang.Object
    • param.Region
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BoxRegion

    abstract class Region
extends java.lang.Object
    A region represents a subset of the valid parameter values. New regions can be produced using the corresponding RegionFactory, or by applying operations on existing ones.
    Author:
    Ernst Moritz Hahn (University of Oxford)
    See Also:
    RegionFactory

      • volume

        abstract BigRational volume()
        Get lower bound of the volume of the region. The volumes of disjoint region which cover the whole parameter space sum up to 1. This implies that the volumes are normalised according to the upper and lower bounds of the parameters.
        Returns:
        lower bound of the volume of this region
